    <h2>WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO NEED?</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>250 g soja amarilla</li>
        <li>2 cucharadas nigari</li>
        <li>Agua</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>DIRECTIONS</h2>
<dl>
    <dt><strong>1- OVEN</strong></dt>
    <dd>Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a large baking sheet with cooking spray.</dd>
    
  <dt><strong>2- </strong></dt>
    <dd>hisk soy sauce, agave, sesame oil, garlic, and ginger together in a bowl until evenly combined.</dd>     
    
  <dt><strong>3- Dry tofu</strong></dt>
    <dd>ently press tofu pieces to release as much water as possible.</dd>
    
  <dt><strong>4- Getting tofu ready</strong></dt>
    <dd>Arrange tofu on the prepared baking sheet and brush with 1/2 of the soy mixture.</dd>
    
  <dt>5- Baking<strong></strong></dt>
    <dd>Bake tofu in the preheated oven for 30 minutes.</dd>
</dl>


            


